    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">Why Choose Free Trial English Lessons?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Learning English online has never been more accessible. With dozens of platforms competing for your attention, it makes sense to test the waters before diving in. Free trial lessons let you experience different teaching styles, platform features, and teacher personalities without spending a single dollar.</p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The problem is that many platforms claim to offer free trials but quietly ask for your credit card number anyway. They bet that you will forget to cancel, or that you will enjoy the service enough to keep paying. This guide cuts through the noise and shows you exactly which platforms let you try before you buy, no credit card required.</p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">By using free trials strategically, you can attend lessons with multiple teachers across different platforms. This hands-on research helps you find the perfect fit for your learning style, schedule, and budget.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">What to Look for in a Free English Trial</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Not all free trials are created equal. Before you sign up anywhere, check these key factors:</p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Lesson Length</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Some platforms offer just 15-minute tasters, while others provide full 30 or even 60-minute sessions for free. Longer trials give you a better sense of whether the teaching style works for you.</p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Teacher Quality</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Check whether the platform lets you choose your trial teacher or if you are assigned randomly. Being able to read teacher profiles and select someone who matches your goals makes the trial much more valuable.</p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Platform Functionality</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">A free trial is also your chance to test the platform itself. Is the booking system easy to use? Does the video quality hold up? Are there any technical issues that would frustrate you daily? Use the trial to answer these questions.</p>
    
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">Hidden Requirements</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">The platforms in this guide genuinely require no credit card upfront. However, always read the fine print. Some platforms ask for payment details to create your account but promise not to charge until you actively subscribe.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-10 mb-4">See Guru: Our Top Pick for No-Card Free Trials</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">See Guru stands out as our top recommendation for free trial English lessons with no credit card required. The platform offers a genuine free trial period where you can book and attend lessons without entering any payment information.</p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">What sets See Guru apart is the quality of their trial experience. Unlike some platforms that assign you a less experienced teacher for trials, See Guru gives you access to their full roster of instructors. This means you can trial lessons with highly-rated teachers before deciding whether to continue.</p>
